A renowned South African artist, Louise Carver, treated fans to an exquisite performance at Yoons@Barnyard on Thursday April 7. Carver’s sold-out show started at around 20:00.  Sitting on stage at her keyboard, she chatted with the audience before welcoming a well-known musician, Simphiwe Kulla, to the stage to perform alongside her. Carver’s performance at Yoons@Barnyard was her first show off her music tour after two years. ALSO READ: Blood drive at Crossing Centre needs your support Her ethereal voice, coupled with Kulla’s background vocals and guitar, was an absolute treat for her fans as everyone tapped their feet during each set, followed by a hearty round of applause. Carver said she loved the Lowveld and even had dreams of a buying a home here.  The show was well received by all who attended.          Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram